<task id="007" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>Commit 3 in-progress namespace fixes per §5.6 (project's first body of work)</title>
    <status>completed-noop</status>
    <estimated-effort>20-30 minutes</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-0, commit, namespace-fixes, testing</tags>
    <parallel-group>0-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches 3 specific test files in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` (if present); these are NAMESPACE-only changes already in working tree. Zero intersection with tasks 001-006 which write only to projects/.../baseline/, decisions/, CLAUDE.md, priority-order.md.</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Per §5.6 (KEEP the 3 in-progress namespace fixes — owner decision recorded in design.md
    Owner Clarifications + project CLAUDE.md Decisions Made), commit the 3 in-progress
    namespace fix edits as the project's first body of work.

    These are LEGITIMATE drift fixes from prior work. Reverting them would be process theater.
    Committing them now saves the re-discovery cost during Phase 1.

    If `git status` shows NO in-progress fixes at task execution time, this task is a NO-OP:
    record "no in-progress fixes existed; §5.6 lock-in is operationally N/A" in current-task.md
    and mark complete. Do NOT invent fixes to satisfy the task title.

    NO production code changes (test-file namespace updates are within `tests/`; preserves NFR-01).
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent performing the project's first commit per §5.6 owner directive.</role>

  <goal>
    Either:
    (a) 3 namespace fix files committed with message "fix(tests): namespace updates per §5.6 lock-in" + `dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` passes on the 3 touched files; OR
    (b) NO-OP path: no in-progress fixes found; current-task.md records "§5.6 lock-in operationally N/A — no in-progress fixes present at execution time".

    Either way, current-task.md is updated and TASK-INDEX.md status changes to complete.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="§5.6">3 namespace fixes are KEEP — first commit of project. If absent, document as N/A.</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No production code changes — only `tests/` files touched</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">Repair, not rewrite — namespace updates are surgical, NOT rewrites; if diff exceeds 50% of any file's lines, HALT and escalate per §4.8</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-11">After fixes, the touched files MUST compile cleanly under `-warnaserror`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-09">`repair-not-rewrite: true` declared in metadata</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/push-to-github/SKILL.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec.md Owner Clarifications (2026-05-31): "Namespace fixes (3 files) — Keep. They're
      legitimate fixes; reverting would be process theater. First commit of project." Per §5.6:
      "the three in-progress namespace fix edits are kept in working tree and become the
      project's first commit." This task executes that owner directive.

      Note: this task was generated at project-pipeline time. The 3 files may or may not actually
      be present in working tree when the task runs (depending on intervening session activity).
      The NO-OP path handles the absence case gracefully without polluting git history with
      placeholder commits.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="none" status="n/a">No upstream; this is independent of baseline capture</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <!-- Up to 3 specific test files in tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ with namespace-only changes.
         Exact paths determined at execution time by `git status`. -->
    <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/* (3 files with namespace-only changes; paths discovered at runtime)</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Run `git status --short` to identify modified files in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. If 0 files modified there, jump to step 7 (NO-OP path).</step>
    <step order="2">Run `git diff tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` to inspect the actual diff. Verify each modified file's changes are NAMESPACE-only: lines starting with `namespace `, `using `, or whitespace adjustments. NO assertion changes. NO method body changes.</step>
    <step order="3">If any file's diff exceeds 50% of its line count OR contains non-namespace edits, HALT. File a §4.8 rewrite escalation request in `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/escalations/rewrite-request-T-007-{filename}.md` and STOP. (This protects NFR-02 even on the project's first commit.)</step>
    <step order="4">Verify the touched files compile: `dotnet build tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj -c Release`. If the 17 known compile-broken files (per baseline) cause failures unrelated to the 3 namespace fixes, that's expected — verify the 3 specific touched files are NOT among the failures (grep error output for the 3 filenames).</step>
    <step order="5">Stage the 3 files explicitly by name: `git add tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/{file1} tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/{file2} tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/{file3}`. Do NOT use `git add -A` or `git add .` (avoids accidentally staging baseline TRX files from task 001).</step>
    <step order="6">Commit with HEREDOC message: `git commit -m "$(cat &lt;&lt;'EOF'
fix(tests): namespace updates per §5.6 lock-in

Three in-progress namespace fix edits committed as the project's first
body of work per design.md §5.6 owner decision. These are legitimate
drift fixes; reverting would be process theater (per spec.md Owner
Clarifications 2026-05-31).

Phase 0 / task 007 / project sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 &lt;noreply@anthropic.com&gt;
EOF
)"`. Verify commit succeeded with `git log -1`.</step>
    <step order="7">NO-OP PATH (executed only when step 1 found 0 modified files in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`): write to `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md`: "Task 007 NO-OP: §5.6 lock-in is operationally N/A — no in-progress namespace fixes were present in working tree at execution time (YYYY-MM-DD). The §5.6 owner decision is documented in design.md and decisions/D-06; no commit is needed because the fixes do not exist locally."</step>
    <step order="8">Update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md` with completion summary (commit hash OR N/A note).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="git">status, diff, add (specific files), commit</tool>
    <tool name="dotnet">build (verify touched files compile)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ (3 files with namespace updates — IF present at runtime)</output>
